    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-05-17T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-05-17T10:00:00-05:00" n="578"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d578">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 300.115G95/15</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-17T15:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 17, 1915, 3 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 2.45 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2105. Your 1529, May 8, and my May 10.<note n="1" xml:id="d578fn1">Neither
                        printed. See Department’s No. 1514, May 6, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref
                            target="#pg_381">p. 381</ref>.</note> Captain <persName>Smith</persName>
                    of S. S. <hi rend="italic">Gulflight</hi>, states that the conversation between
                    the late Captain <persName>Gunter</persName> of <hi rend="italic">Gulflight</hi>
                    and the skipper of British patrol boat <hi rend="italic">Filey</hi> was to the
                    effect that Captain <persName>Gunter</persName>, in replying that the ship was
                    bound to Rouen, asked when he could secure a French pilot. The reply of the
                    patrol boat was that he could not get one there and directed the <hi
                        rend="italic">Gulflight</hi> to follow the patrols to the Bishop Rock.</p>
                <p>The British Admiralty states in reply to my inquiry that the ships which did the
                    convoying are now at sea out of communication, but the details will be obtained
                    as soon as they return to port.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
